              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "2NEDUTR"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " the Utrecht 6 MV tandem accelerator"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SPECM"
                ],
                "institute": "2NEDUTR"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The target was prepared by bombarding",
                " a 40 mug/cm**2 aluminium foil with S-33 ions",
                "accelerator to 40 keV in a mass separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " the Utrecht split-pole magnetic spectrograph by",
                "one 15 mm long and seven 30 mm long, 0.6 mm thick",
                "positive-sensitive detectors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " at 60 degree monitored elastically scattered",
                "deuterons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.Teflon foils of 0.5-1.0 mm thickness",
                "placed 1 mm in front of the PSD's stopped undesired",
                "reaction products such as deuterons and alpha-particles",
                "and degraded the initial proton energy up to 21 MeV in",
                "order to increase the fraction of the total energy,",
                "dissipated in the thin detectors.",
                "*By authors*.To normalize the data to absolute cross",
                "sections, a target thickness measurement was performed",
                "by means of 3 MeV deuterons, elastically scattered from",
                "S-33, for which it was assumed that the cross sections",
                "was due to Rutherford scattering only."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The starting material was natural sulphur. The S-33",
                "was collected on an area of 1.5 mm*3 mm and the target",
                "had an estimated thickness of 10 mug/cm**2.",
                "The spectrum of elastically scattered deuterons showed",
                "that the target contained 23% S-32, most probably due",
                "to the admixture of H-S-32 ions in the mass separator",
                "beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
